window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>In the tradition of M. Night Shyamalan and Stephen King, <i>Bloodhound</i> is a coming-of-age suspense drama about Jay Pulver, a trans college student who discovers he has mysteriously acquired superhuman abilities when he accidentally kills his sister’s ex-boyfriend. Recruited by a brilliant but eccentric scientist at the FBI, Jay is tasked with employing his unique powers to track down a domestic terrorist group currently setting off bombs around Washington, DC.</p> <p>As Jay comes to grips with his new abilities, he must grapple with his own family trauma—and what he's internalized about what it means to be a man—before he loses himself and everything that matters to him.</p> <p>Available in Dolby Atmos on Audible.</p>"; 
